shared_text:
ACCOUNTS.GOOGLE.COM
Google Forms - create and analyze surveys, for free.

Josh And-Krissy Grover shared a link to the group: Cass Lake-Bena Elementary.
August 27 at 11:47 AM ·

CLBE Families - I will be sending a comprehensive update very soon. However, we are excited to say that our elementary students K-4 will have the opportunity to use a Chromebook at home for distance learning. 4th Grade students will be issued a device. However, K-3 is by parent request. K-3 parents/guardians, please fill out this form if you'd like a device for your child. By filling the form out, you agree to provide support to your child for logging in and that you have access to the internet. We also ask the you please take care of these devices. Dr. G.

post_text:
#CLBSPanthers! The Distance Learning Opt-in Form is here! You can access is at the link below.

Please complete this form, if you would like to opt-in to our distance learning option. Filling out this form means that your child will do all their learning from home under the guidance of Cass Lake-Bena Schools Teachers. If you have more than one child, please fill out a form for each child.

During the school year, if you change your mind, and would like your child to attend in an in-person or hybrid model, you will be provided opportunities to make that change. Thank you for helping us plan for the 2020-2021 school year!

post_text:
Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.

Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

The Cass Lake Area Learning Center would like to send a HUGE shout out to the FABULOUS staff on Teacher Appreciation Week! Lisa, Rhonda, Roberta, Melissa and Krissy

post_text:
A Message From Rochelle Johnson, Superintendent of Cass Lake-Bena Schools:

Dear families,
As you are aware the state is on a 2 week
stay put order. This will not affect the child care or food service plans. We will be delivering all intial school work for our distance learning plan this Friday, March 27th, using our buses to deliver. These buses will be using the Monday transportation schedule on their normal routes. Parents or Guardians must meet the bus at the stop to receive these materials for their students. This delivery includes Middle and High School students only. Elementary student materials will be mailed. Thank you for your support. As always, please see the district website for more details.

The high school took a group of 43 students to the Career Expo Day put on by Bridges Career Academies at Central Lakes College.

Students were exposed to over 200 different careers where they could do hands-on activities to experience what it may be like to actually work in one of those careers.

Students got to try things like virtual reality, welding, nursing skills, looking at counterfeit money, live food demos, bending sheet metal, making ethernet cables, and much more!

#CLBSPanthers

post_text:
Congratulations to Robotics Coach Mr. Jesse Frost!

This past weekend at the Lake Superior Regional, Coach Frost was awarded the Woodie Flowers award. Recipients for this award are nominated by students (in this case, Ms. Sharon McGuire of 3134) and is a very prestigious award that no other mentor from the north has won. The Accelerators are incredibly excited and proud that Coach Frost is being recognized for all of his hard work.

Woodie Flowers Finalist Award is presented to an outstanding Mentor in the Robotics Competition who best leads, inspires, teaches, and empowers their team using excellent communication skills.

Thanks for all your hard work and dedication! When you see Coach Frost, be sure to give him a big congratulations!
#CLBSPanthers

Students in Mr. Bents’ class are learning about plate tectonics and how volcanoes are formed. The students got to make volcanoes out of paper mache painted them.

Last week they got to erupt them and see a resemblance of how the lava comes out of the volcanoes that resemble the three different types of volcanoes. Hands-on learning activities are so much fun!
#CLBSPanthers

Families of current 5th-7th graders, please join us on Thursday, February 13th at 6:00pm for a 25-minute parent informational meeting about the Washington D.C. trip.

A tour director will be there to meet you and explain more about this once-in-a-lifetime adventure to Washington, D.C. and Mt. Vernon during the summer of 2021.

Please consider joining us if you have any interest at all, as there will be FREE pizza! Don't miss out!

This the link to the video shown to the students this week!
https://www.facebook.com/worldclassrooms/videos/2373814996201746/

Please contact Mrs. Kandel at jkandel@isd115.net with any questions.
#CLBSPanthers
